description: Mkango Resources Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, explores for and develops rare earth elements and associated minerals in the Republic of Malawi, Africa. It explores for uranium, tantalum, niobium, zircon, nickel, cobalt, rutile, graphite, and gold ores. The company's flagship project is the Songwe Hill property within the Phalombe exploration license located in southeast Malawi. It also holds 100% interests in the Thambani, Chimimbe Hill, and Mchinji licenses. The company is based in Vancouver, Canada.
ceo: Mr. William  Dawes BSc., CFA, MIMMM, MSc.
